---
description: "TypeScript conventions for AFNM mods. Activate when writing or reviewing TypeScript code."
globs:
  - "src/**/*.ts"
  - "src/**/*.tsx"
alwaysApply: false
---

See `.agents/skills/typescript-afnm/SKILL.md`.

Key rules:
- Strict mode is on. Never disable it.
- Always optional-chain ModAPI access: `window.modAPI?.hooks?.onLocationEnter?.()`
- Never use `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow with type guards.
- React/MUI are externalized — never bundle them.
- Import game types from `afnm-types`.
- Run `bun run typecheck` before committing.
- Formatting: 2 spaces, single quotes, trailing commas, LF (`.prettierrc`).
